Text.string: A head without a body. I'm in.
A head without a body. Sure, why not?
A head without a body. This cannot stand!
A head without a body. Lotta my best nights started this way.

Ahhhhhhhh! Damn varkids!||—Oh, I'm... I'm all right, heh. What fortune that you came along, adventurer! I am Wren, scion of Alkonost, the most legendary explorer in all the galaxy. Surely you've heard of her.

Long ago, Alkonost sought the ancient Eridian city of Azamak-mur. Although it has been decades since we received her last transmission, I am confident she has noted our presence and is preparing a wondrous celebration of my arrival!
Hmm, strange. No welcoming party. And the door is locked. Well, Alkonost the Reclaimer can't just let ANYONE into Azamak-mur. A moment, adventurer.
Drat, looks like those nasty varkids begunked my hoverjets. Go on ahead, adventurer. Seek out Alkonost and the expedition.
And tell Alkonost to send her best medic bots to me, for I am... truly begunked.

I cannot wait to reunite with Alkonost and her expedition. Lark, rogue-bot with legendary stealth protocols. Shrike, the bruiser-bot with unrivaled torque and expanded RAM. Saying nothing of Karapius of the Silversense and Noratio the Bold, whose songs I downloaded as a fledgling bot!
Hmm. My sensors indicate that Lark is nearby! Lark? Lark, do you hear me? Beep if you're injured! Where are you, Lark?!
Oh, Lark... torn asunder by varkids. Nasty wretches.
Beep... beep... beeeeeeeeeep...
Lark is gone. One moment. I will try to power Lark remotely to glean what I may of his death and the expedition's fate.

Lark... slain, but the party presses on towards Azamak-mur to rekindle the flame of this forgotten Eridian city. Today we reached an odd door whose runes would only alight when struck by fire through rings thrice. Typhon DeLeon and his Eridian expert, Leda, have proven useful companions. And so, we press on, tiny lights into the dark.
That's a hard nope.
Eh, not ringing a bell.
I have not.
Not really, no.
Open the door, adventurer! The reclaimed city of Azamak-mur awaits!
Heed Alkonost's words! Line up three rings and and shoot, friend!
Shoot wisely. Three rings, yes, yes, line them up!
Do as Leda did, and find three rings!
You must shoot the runes through the rings!
Well met! Now, to Alkonost, who at this moment has surely noticed our presence and is sending her personal retinue to welcome us to Azamak-mur!
I sense a signal coming from that room.

Our party is in peril. Typhon has barred the doors, and Leda searches for an alternate path out of this place—but their stomachs empty, and our processors dim. In despair, the two agree to forever-bond and seek a ring, so they may be joined at least in death.
Alkonost! There is another signal, adventurer.
Oops.
Ugh. These hands...
An accident...
Crap.

The varkids scatter as it comes... the demon of the deep, Lagromar. Left to fester in the shadows of this cursed place. Now we are trapped. A mistranslated rune is the culprit. This isn't an Eridian city, but a necropolis!
Alkonost! Trapped. And now I fear her party has been lost.
Did... you hear that?

Well, no matter. I am on a quest to reunite with Alkonost, but my head was riven from my frame by those nasty varkids. It's just inside those doors. There's a lever around here somewhere, but until I'm reunited with my frame, you will have to be my arms.
The varkids fly! Awakened by a stirring in the deep. I sense activity in the Great Hall! Quickly, adventurer! Alkonost will protect you!
(big growl)
(big growl)
Lagromar, defeat that foul demon and avenge my ancestor!
Alkonost's head! Recover it, adventurer!

The party is undone. I held the door as Typhon and Leda made their escape. Forever-bonded. Married, using the ring from my own power coil for Leda, and my exhaust pipe ring for Typhon. Now, I expire... so that they may enkindle a light in the dark...
It is done. Alkonost has fallen. A moment, adventurer. I believe I have found you a way out.
Return to me. I have something for you.

Eridium... I had hoped it to be an offering to Alkonost and Azamak-mur, but both are lost. What sorrow, what sorrow! All that's left to me now is seek out the fabled city of Iktok-gofeldor-maruun. Surely you've heard of it? No? What sorrow!
Beep.
Excellent work, adventurer. Now, come pick me up!
My thanks. Now, after you find my frame, I will regale you with tales of Alkonost's adventures, and the treasure she sought.
The beeping's close... too close. Whatever that means.
It's close. Gotta be somewhere around here. Fists ready.
The source of the beeping is nearby. But where? And why?
Gettin' louder. I should say hello. Beep, beep. Beeeeeep! There.
Not much further now!

We have reached the entrance of Azamak-mur. DeLeon searches for coordinates to the Eridian homeworld, but the treasure I desire is Azamak-mur itself, for I feel a kinship to the Eridians, and dream of a home for my people.

Much better! Now, adventurer... heed the call and aid me in finding Alkonost, defender of Basorod. Alkonost the Unfragmented? Nothing? Truly? Why, she is the Typhon DeLeon of robotic explorers. In fact, the two led this very expedition together, a rare partnership of bot and human!
